1
00:01:44,920 --> 00:01:47,120
I have a rough idea why you’re here to see me.

2
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:51,120
I also deeply sympathize with that lady’s situation.

3
00:01:51,359 --> 00:01:52,359
I feel sorry for her.

4
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:54,200
But you’ve misunderstood.

5
00:01:54,519 --> 00:01:55,640
I don’t know her.

6
00:01:56,359 --> 00:01:57,640
I’ve never contacted her either.

7
00:01:58,959 --> 00:02:00,519
From the 20th of last month

8
00:02:00,519 --> 00:02:02,000
until 6 a.m. the day before yesterday,

9
00:02:02,280 --> 00:02:03,319
I wasn’t in the country.

10
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:17,000
Any other questions?

11
00:02:18,759 --> 00:02:20,039
Are you sure you don’t know her?

12
00:02:22,879 --> 00:02:24,120
Let me show you something.

13
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:28,319
This is you, right?

14
00:02:30,879 --> 00:02:31,639
Does it matter?

15
00:02:39,240 --> 00:02:40,120
How did he know

16
00:02:40,120 --> 00:02:41,479
we’re investigating this case?

17
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:43,400
He clearly came prepared.

18
00:02:44,120 --> 00:02:45,520
Doesn’t he have a secretary?

19
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:48,599
That secretary does more than just secretarial work.

20
00:02:48,759 --> 00:02:49,639
She also acts as a pimp.

21
00:02:49,639 --> 00:02:51,159
She has to gather all kinds of inside information too.

22
00:02:51,159 --> 00:02:51,960
That’s exhausting.

23
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:52,800
Alright.

24
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:54,080
Let’s go.

25
00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:03,120
Can you sleep now?

26
00:03:07,439 --> 00:03:08,599
I can’t sleep.

27
00:03:10,159 --> 00:03:12,000
The more you talk, the less I can sleep.

28
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:15,479
How about you sing me a song?

29
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:17,199
Sing?

30
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:20,080
I don’t know many songs.

31
00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:22,520
Just sing one for me.

32
00:03:25,080 --> 00:03:26,280
Alright, alright.

33
00:03:26,479 --> 00:03:27,240
Okay, okay, I’ll sing.

34
00:03:31,039 --> 00:03:40,000
So many storms, so many springs and autumns...

35
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:43,479
If you sing that, I’ll be even less able to sleep.

36
00:03:45,879 --> 00:03:46,599
Then what should I do?

37
00:03:46,599 --> 00:03:48,560
I told you, I don’t know many songs.

38
00:03:49,439 --> 00:03:50,520
Pick another one.

39
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:53,000
Sing a children’s song instead.

40
00:03:54,159 --> 00:03:55,360
A children’s song?

41
00:04:02,319 --> 00:04:09,840
The moon is bright, the wind is still

42
00:04:11,719 --> 00:04:18,160
Leaves cover the window lattice

43
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:28,319
Crickets chirp with a metallic sound

44
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:37,000
Just like the sound of zither strings

45
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:41,399
Tingting

46
00:04:42,519 --> 00:04:43,360
Are you asleep?

47
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:50,839
Good night

48
00:05:06,319 --> 00:05:07,199
Awake again

49
00:05:07,519 --> 00:05:08,120
Hello

50
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:10,079
Another one of my people has gone missing

51
00:05:10,439 --> 00:05:11,720
It must be that bastard's doing

52
00:05:12,120 --> 00:05:12,920
Where are you?

53
00:05:22,759 --> 00:05:23,560
What's going on?

54
00:05:24,480 --> 00:05:25,800
Someone named Wang Hui has gone missing again

55
00:05:26,399 --> 00:05:27,480
It's been over two hours

56
00:05:27,839 --> 00:05:28,879
What exactly happened?

57
00:05:29,519 --> 00:05:30,279
Let's hurry right now

58
00:05:30,279 --> 00:05:32,600
Don't rush, explain the situation first

59
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:34,800
Yes, here's what happened

60
00:05:35,399 --> 00:05:37,319
I've been telling them not to go out these past two days

61
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:38,120
But Wang Hui

62
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:39,360
She wouldn't listen, insisted on going out

63
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:40,120
I'm going to the bathroom

64
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:07,879
Did she go out to get her bag?

65
00:06:08,759 --> 00:06:09,720
How would I know?

66
00:06:12,759 --> 00:06:13,360
Turns out,

67
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:15,720
she got into a cement mixer truck.

68
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:16,000
Go.

69
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:16,759
Wang Hui.

70
00:06:17,120 --> 00:06:18,519
I ran after her as fast as I could.

71
00:06:19,319 --> 00:06:20,040
Wang Hui.

72
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:21,439
Wang Hui.

73
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:24,120
I ran a long way, but I couldn't catch up.

74
00:06:24,759 --> 00:06:25,680
I thought to myself,

75
00:06:26,839 --> 00:06:27,800
if she left, then she left.

76
00:06:29,079 --> 00:06:30,240
So I went back first.

77
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:32,959
But I kept thinking,

78
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:35,319
it's been over two hours.

79
00:06:35,319 --> 00:06:36,800
She should be back by now, right?

80
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:38,839
But I haven't seen her.

81
00:06:39,079 --> 00:06:40,199
So I called her.

82
00:06:40,839 --> 00:06:41,759
Her phone was off.

83
00:06:42,839 --> 00:06:43,800
Did you check at home?

84
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:45,519
I haven't had the chance yet.

85
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:47,360
Did you see clearly?

86
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:48,519
It was a cement mixer truck.

87
00:06:48,519 --> 00:06:49,399
A cement mixer truck.

88
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:51,000
Do you remember the license plate number?

89
00:06:51,199 --> 00:06:52,800
Hai A 99875.

90
00:06:53,199 --> 00:06:54,000
Repeat it.

91
00:06:54,519 --> 00:06:56,879
Hai A99 99875, that's right.

92
00:06:56,879 --> 00:06:58,279
You two, check the license plate number.

93
00:06:58,279 --> 00:07:00,000
See which concrete mixing station it belongs to.

94
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,600
If you find anything, don't act rashly.

95
00:07:01,759 --> 00:07:02,519
Wait for instructions from the team.

96
00:07:02,519 --> 00:07:02,959
Did you hear me?

97
00:07:02,959 --> 00:07:03,439
Yes, yes.

98
00:07:03,439 --> 00:07:04,160
Hurry up and go.

99
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:05,680
Where is her home?

100
00:07:11,319 --> 00:07:11,959
Wang Hui.

101
00:07:14,120 --> 00:07:15,319
Is Wang Hui at home?

102
00:07:22,920 --> 00:07:23,879
Who are you looking for?

103
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:25,600
Hey, kid.

104
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:27,199
Is Wang Hui here?

105
00:07:28,399 --> 00:07:29,040
She’s not here.

106
00:07:30,319 --> 00:07:31,199
Where did she go?

107
00:07:32,199 --> 00:07:33,279
She’s working the night shift.

108
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:37,920
Kid, I’m a police officer.

109
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:39,680
Can you open the door for me?

110
00:07:40,319 --> 00:07:42,480
You say you’re a police officer—do you have a badge?

111
00:07:42,480 --> 00:07:43,199
Look.

112
00:07:45,519 --> 00:07:46,439
You really are a police officer.

113
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,000
Is Wang Hui your mom?

114
00:07:54,759 --> 00:07:55,560
She’s not home.

115
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:57,439
She’s not home, she’s working the night shift.

116
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:00,399
Can we come in and have a look?

117
00:08:07,199 --> 00:08:08,240
Are you home alone?

118
00:08:08,439 --> 00:08:09,240
Yes.

119
00:08:10,519 --> 00:08:11,560
Let me take a look, okay?

120
00:08:18,399 --> 00:08:19,639
Is this your mom’s room?

121
00:08:40,919 --> 00:08:41,600
Hey, kid.

122
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:44,799
When your mom left today,

123
00:08:44,919 --> 00:08:46,600
was there anything different from usual?

124
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:49,519
Nothing was different.

125
00:08:50,879 --> 00:08:51,759
Qianqian.

126
00:08:51,919 --> 00:08:53,879
Can you bring me that yellow floral jacket?

127
00:08:53,879 --> 00:08:54,559
Okay.

128
00:08:59,320 --> 00:09:00,279
Go do your homework now.

129
00:09:00,279 --> 00:09:00,960
Okay.

130
00:09:01,759 --> 00:09:04,480
If I do my homework, she’ll make me food.

131
00:09:12,399 --> 00:09:14,799
Qianqian, eat first, have your meal.

132
00:09:14,799 --> 00:09:16,039
Do your homework after you finish eating.

133
00:09:19,399 --> 00:09:20,559
Tidy up over there.

134
00:09:20,559 --> 00:09:22,960
I ended up eating the meal I cooked.

135
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:26,039
She didn't eat a single bite and left in a hurry.

136
00:09:26,320 --> 00:09:28,000
After you finish eating, quickly finish your homework.

137
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,000
Mom is going out.

138
00:09:29,159 --> 00:09:31,200
She also told me to close the door tightly.

139
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:31,600
Bye, Mom.

140
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:32,919
Don't let strangers in.

141
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:34,399
Do your homework properly.

142
00:09:34,399 --> 00:09:35,120
After I leave in a bit,

143
00:09:35,120 --> 00:09:36,080
lock the door well.

144
00:09:36,799 --> 00:09:38,600
Lock up and go to bed early. I'm leaving.

145
00:09:42,399 --> 00:09:44,279
Did anyone come to the house today?

146
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:45,559
No.

147
00:09:48,799 --> 00:09:49,879
You're a police officer too.

148
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:54,279
You've always lived here with your mom?

149
00:09:54,879 --> 00:09:57,600
Yes, my mom works the night shift.

150
00:09:58,360 --> 00:09:59,919
She's not home at this time.

151
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:07,720
Alright, we'll head out first.

152
00:10:07,759 --> 00:10:08,600
Listen to your mom.

153
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:10,200
Lock the door in a bit.

154
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:11,200
Don't open the door to strangers.

155
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:16,399
Uncle.

156
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:18,399
Did something happen to my mom?

157
00:10:22,759 --> 00:10:24,080
Your mom has to work overtime.

158
00:10:24,240 --> 00:10:26,039
She'll be back a bit later than usual.

159
00:10:26,879 --> 00:10:27,879
So, come with me.

160
00:10:28,159 --> 00:10:29,200
I'll take care of you today.

161
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:31,720
You haven't shown me your police badge yet.

162
00:10:32,120 --> 00:10:33,960
The badge is in my bag.

163
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:37,360
How are you going to take care of me?

164
00:10:37,399 --> 00:10:39,039
Don't worry about it. I have a child too.

165
00:10:39,039 --> 00:10:40,000
She's a girl as well.

166
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,399
And she told me before,

167
00:10:42,879 --> 00:10:44,159
she's wanted to change jobs for a while.

168
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:45,799
I was the one who convinced her to stay until the end of the month.

169
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:48,919
I owe her for that. Come on.

170
00:10:50,720 --> 00:10:51,840
This way, put it on your back.

171
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:57,000
You're "Dog Thing," aren't you?

172
00:10:57,919 --> 00:10:58,559
What?

173
00:11:01,159 --> 00:11:02,919
In my mom's phone,

174
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:05,120
your name is "Dog Thing 515."

175
00:11:05,240 --> 00:11:06,360
What's 515?

176
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:10,320
My birthday.

177
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:14,399
How about this:

178
00:11:14,679 --> 00:11:15,639
You two come with me.

179
00:11:16,679 --> 00:11:17,759
Put the clothes on the child.

180
00:11:17,759 --> 00:11:18,240
Come on.

181
00:11:19,480 --> 00:11:20,039
Dong Xiang.

182
00:11:20,240 --> 00:11:22,320
Turn yourself in after sunrise.

183
00:11:33,159 --> 00:11:34,279
What's wrong? No one's answering?

184
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:35,159
The phone's off.

185
00:11:36,120 --> 00:11:37,399
Let me see what his name is.

186
00:11:38,759 --> 00:11:39,440
Chen Jian.

187
00:11:42,519 --> 00:11:44,480
Attention to everyone on the road, attention.

188
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:45,960
Report immediately if you see car number seven.

189
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:47,519
Report immediately if you see car number seven.

190
00:11:48,519 --> 00:11:50,519
Do you have a photo of him on file here?

191
00:11:50,600 --> 00:11:51,399
ID card photo.

192
00:11:51,399 --> 00:11:52,039
Yes.

193
00:11:54,960 --> 00:11:55,399
Here.

194
00:11:57,960 --> 00:12:00,000
Chen Jian, born in 1976.

195
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:01,399
Where does he usually live?

196
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:18,240
Here.

197
00:12:35,840 --> 00:12:37,000
There's a window in the back.

198
00:12:56,320 --> 00:12:56,919
Ziming.

199
00:12:57,399 --> 00:12:58,799
What's up? What do you mean? Come on.

200
00:13:01,039 --> 00:13:03,360
Lei, sorry to trouble you.

201
00:13:03,679 --> 00:13:04,600
Take care of them.

202
00:13:05,159 --> 00:13:05,919
No problem.

203
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:09,240
You go ahead and do your thing, hurry.

204
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:10,080
Alright, you don't need to worry about this.

205
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:10,960
Get them something to eat.

206
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:11,679
Don't worry.

207
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:13,399
Um, sit here.

208
00:13:13,399 --> 00:13:14,159
Sit wherever you like.

209
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:15,519
It's already this late.

210
00:13:15,519 --> 00:13:17,240
I'll just make you something simple.

211
00:13:17,639 --> 00:13:18,200
Don't go to any trouble.

212
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:19,200
Alright, alright.

213
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:22,960
You guys keep watch near his house.

214
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:23,840
Are you cold? Let the team know.

215
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:24,440
I'm not cold.

216
00:13:24,720 --> 00:13:26,240
Don't make any moves until we know the situation.

217
00:13:26,279 --> 00:13:27,120
I'm coming over right now.

218
00:13:38,279 --> 00:13:39,080
There's someone inside.

219
00:13:47,679 --> 00:13:48,639
What's going on?

220
00:13:56,399 --> 00:13:57,200
I'll go take a look.

221
00:13:58,960 --> 00:13:59,759
Be careful.

222
00:14:16,639 --> 00:14:17,440
What's going on?

223
00:14:19,519 --> 00:14:20,759
Did he find something?

224
00:14:28,159 --> 00:14:29,080
The master hasn't arrived yet.

225
00:14:29,519 --> 00:14:30,840
If we wait for the master, he'll run away.

226
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:31,679
Let's take him down.

227
00:14:42,120 --> 00:14:42,720
Open the door.

228
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:44,639
Is there a gas leak in your place?

229
00:14:44,639 --> 00:14:45,639
We can all smell it in our place.

230
00:14:46,120 --> 00:14:46,919
Gas.

231
00:14:46,960 --> 00:14:48,080
Hurry, hurry, open the door!

232
00:14:51,080 --> 00:14:52,240
Don't move, police!

233
00:14:52,240 --> 00:14:53,120
Help!

234
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:55,000
Someone help! Help!

235
00:14:55,159 --> 00:14:56,240
Help! Who are you? Don't move!

236
00:14:56,240 --> 00:14:57,559
Don't move, police!

237
00:14:58,039 --> 00:14:59,600
Chen Jian, right? Where is Wang Hui?

238
00:14:59,919 --> 00:15:01,039
Who's Chen Jian?

239
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:01,679
Making it up.

240
00:15:03,559 --> 00:15:04,639
Where is Wang Hui?

241
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:06,080
Who's Wang Hui?

242
00:15:06,639 --> 00:15:08,919
I'm Yu Baiping.

243
00:15:09,159 --> 00:15:10,240
If you don't believe me, check my ID.

244
00:15:10,320 --> 00:15:11,120
Under the pillow.

245
00:15:11,120 --> 00:15:11,600
Look for it.

246
00:15:13,720 --> 00:15:14,879
You really are Yu Baiping.

247
00:15:14,879 --> 00:15:15,559
What's going on?

248
00:15:15,559 --> 00:15:16,720
Isn't this 902?

249
00:15:16,720 --> 00:15:18,279
This is 901.

250
00:15:18,519 --> 00:15:19,759
902 is next door.

251
00:15:19,759 --> 00:15:21,799
Who changed my door number?

252
00:15:21,799 --> 00:15:23,480
Then why do you keep turning the lights on and off in the middle of the night?

253
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:25,360
Can't I have insomnia?

254
00:15:25,360 --> 00:15:26,159
Don't move.

255
00:15:27,120 --> 00:15:28,159
The police are hitting people!

256
00:15:28,159 --> 00:15:29,200
Don't move! Help!

257
00:15:29,200 --> 00:15:30,480
What are you standing there for? Call and check!

258
00:15:30,480 --> 00:15:31,039
Okay.

259
00:15:53,360 --> 00:15:54,080
Liu Ziming

260
00:15:54,679 --> 00:15:55,840
How do you manage your team?

261
00:15:56,360 --> 00:15:57,440
Who allowed them to act on their own?

262
00:15:57,440 --> 00:15:58,799
Captain Huang, please don't worry.

263
00:15:58,799 --> 00:15:59,759
How can I not be worried?

264
00:15:59,759 --> 00:16:00,840
It's lucky no one got hurt.

265
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:01,879
What if someone had been injured?

266
00:16:01,879 --> 00:16:02,600
Arrest them first.

267
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:03,639
Have them write a self-criticism when we get back.

268
00:16:03,639 --> 00:16:05,000
Handle it as it should be handled.

269
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:06,240
You think you can get away?

270
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:07,159
Captain Huang

271
00:16:07,159 --> 00:16:08,799
The foreman said he saw that car.

272
00:16:08,799 --> 00:16:09,679
It's on National Highway 108.

273
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:12,480
It's currently stopped at the 503 section, heading east to west.

274
00:16:13,200 --> 00:16:13,639
Let's go.

275
00:16:13,639 --> 00:16:14,159
Get in the car.

276
00:18:16,160 --> 00:18:17,359
Let me go.

277
00:18:17,359 --> 00:18:19,319
I have a child.

278
00:18:26,440 --> 00:18:27,759
Help!

279
00:18:28,519 --> 00:18:29,799
Help!

280
00:18:31,240 --> 00:18:32,559
Help!

281
00:18:33,680 --> 00:18:35,119
Help! Help!

282
00:18:35,119 --> 00:18:36,079
Up ahead, hurry!

283
00:18:37,119 --> 00:18:38,480
Help!

