540
00:33:05,960 --> 00:33:07,279
That's our home.

541
00:33:10,400 --> 00:33:11,839
We'll get the keys next month.

542
00:33:12,559 --> 00:33:14,079
The deed is in your name.

543
00:33:18,759 --> 00:33:20,960
I promised you when we got married

544
00:33:22,240 --> 00:33:24,960
that when we had money, we'd buy our own place. Did you forget?

545
00:33:26,680 --> 00:33:27,960
When did you buy it?

546
00:33:28,480 --> 00:33:30,279
It's been over a year.

547
00:33:31,359 --> 00:33:33,079
Every time, I came to check on it by myself, in secret.

548
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:37,400
From laying the foundation, to building up to the third floor,

549
00:33:37,440 --> 00:33:38,559
then the fifth floor,

550
00:33:39,279 --> 00:33:40,559
then to our floor,

551
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:43,559
and now it's finally topped out.

552
00:33:46,200 --> 00:33:47,359
Where did the money come from?

553
00:33:48,559 --> 00:33:50,680
I borrowed it from Cao Lei, Liu Yang, and the others.

554
00:33:51,200 --> 00:33:54,000
Every month when I get paid, I pay them back a little.

555
00:33:54,200 --> 00:33:55,279
There's not much left to pay off.

556
00:34:01,359 --> 00:34:02,279
No crying.

557
00:34:02,759 --> 00:34:04,039
You just finished your postpartum recovery.

558
00:34:04,079 --> 00:34:05,839
If your mom finds out, she'll kill me.

559
00:34:06,759 --> 00:34:08,039
You've worked so hard.

560
00:34:09,719 --> 00:34:10,719
It's not hard at all.

561
00:34:26,519 --> 00:34:27,280
Ziming is back.

562
00:34:27,280 --> 00:34:27,760
Mom.

563
00:34:27,760 --> 00:34:28,480
You're back.

564
00:34:28,480 --> 00:34:29,039
You're back.

565
00:34:29,039 --> 00:34:30,119
Wash your hands and hold the baby.

566
00:34:31,639 --> 00:34:32,800
All the guests have left.

567
00:34:32,800 --> 00:34:33,440
They've left.

568
00:34:33,440 --> 00:34:35,039
If they didn't leave, would they stay here for the New Year?

569
00:34:35,960 --> 00:34:36,880
You haven't eaten yet, have you?

570
00:34:37,440 --> 00:34:38,800
Have some cake to tide you over.

571
00:34:38,920 --> 00:34:39,800
I'm not in a hurry.

572
00:34:39,800 --> 00:34:40,559
I'll wash my hands first.

573
00:34:40,559 --> 00:34:41,480
Let me hold the baby.

574
00:34:41,559 --> 00:34:42,360
Son.

575
00:34:42,440 --> 00:34:43,599
Ziming, Ziming.

576
00:34:43,599 --> 00:34:45,800
I have something I want to ask you to help me with.

577
00:34:45,800 --> 00:34:46,320
Go ahead.

578
00:34:46,320 --> 00:34:48,119
That dog from Sister Wang's house next door—

579
00:34:48,119 --> 00:34:49,679
It was taken away by the dog-catching team.

580
00:34:49,679 --> 00:34:51,000
Can you help me get it back?

581
00:34:51,280 --> 00:34:52,519
Did the dog have a license?

582
00:34:52,519 --> 00:34:54,199
If it had a license, they wouldn't have taken it.

583
00:34:54,280 --> 00:34:55,719
Just get a license and that's it.

584
00:34:56,280 --> 00:34:57,400
It's an old dog.

585
00:34:57,400 --> 00:34:58,599
It's over ten years old.

586
00:34:58,639 --> 00:35:00,320
It might die in a few days anyway.

587
00:35:00,320 --> 00:35:01,480
Why bother getting a license?

588
00:35:01,639 --> 00:35:03,119
Ziming, don't listen to your mom.

589
00:35:03,199 --> 00:35:04,639
Their dog not only doesn't have a license,

590
00:35:04,639 --> 00:35:05,559
it also bites people when it goes out.

591
00:35:05,559 --> 00:35:06,679
Someone called the police to have it taken away.

592
00:35:06,679 --> 00:35:08,639
Nonsense! So what if it bit someone?

593
00:35:08,920 --> 00:35:10,280
The dog didn't do it on purpose.

594
00:35:10,280 --> 00:35:12,039
If a dog doesn't know better, do people not know better either?

595
00:35:13,039 --> 00:35:15,239
Ziming, Ziming, you have to help me with this.

596
00:35:15,239 --> 00:35:16,639
I've already promised them.

597
00:35:16,639 --> 00:35:17,719
Mom, you have to do me this favor.

598
00:35:17,719 --> 00:35:18,840
Mom, I can't handle this.

599
00:35:18,840 --> 00:35:20,400
Mom, don't make things difficult for Ziming.

600
00:35:20,400 --> 00:35:20,960
Daddy, hug.

601
00:35:20,960 --> 00:35:22,519
You can't even handle people, and now you want to take care of a dog?

602
00:35:22,519 --> 00:35:24,079
Happy birthday, son.

603
00:35:24,079 --> 00:35:25,039
Hold it up, hold it up.

604
00:35:25,079 --> 00:35:27,239
Just say that's our own dog.

605
00:35:27,960 --> 00:35:28,960
Dian Dian, say "Daddy."

606
00:35:28,960 --> 00:35:30,960
Say "Daddy," say "Daddy," say "Daddy."

607
00:35:30,960 --> 00:35:31,519
Such a good kid.

608
00:35:31,920 --> 00:35:33,400
He calls everyone "Daddy" when he goes out.

609
00:35:33,400 --> 00:35:34,480
Why doesn't he call you when he sees you?

610
00:35:34,480 --> 00:35:35,679
Dad, stop talking nonsense.

611
00:35:36,840 --> 00:35:38,960
Don't cry, don't cry, don't cry.

612
00:35:38,960 --> 00:35:39,559
Come here, come here.

613
00:35:39,559 --> 00:35:41,679
See, you’re never home, so he’s become shy around you.

614
00:35:45,880 --> 00:35:48,800
Don't cry, don't cry, don't cry.

615
00:35:49,199 --> 00:35:50,039
Alright, alright.

616
00:35:52,519 --> 00:35:53,320
Captain Huang,

617
00:35:53,960 --> 00:35:54,800
You mean

618
00:35:54,800 --> 00:35:56,480
you want us to drop everything

619
00:35:56,719 --> 00:35:57,960
and go investigate a stolen manhole cover?

620
00:35:59,800 --> 00:36:01,480
It's not just one stolen manhole cover.

621
00:36:01,480 --> 00:36:03,159
There are a lot, okay?

622
00:36:03,880 --> 00:36:05,159
This is a series of cases.

623
00:36:05,159 --> 00:36:06,039
Just last Friday,

624
00:36:06,360 --> 00:36:08,920
a whole row of manhole covers disappeared along Yanhe East Road.

625
00:36:09,000 --> 00:36:09,920
And just a few days later,

626
00:36:09,920 --> 00:36:13,000
the manhole covers on Hongtai Road were stolen too.

627
00:36:13,760 --> 00:36:15,760
Didn't you see it online and in the newspapers?

628
00:36:16,599 --> 00:36:18,719
Public opinion is blowing up.

629
00:36:19,039 --> 00:36:20,840
If you want to calm public opinion,

630
00:36:20,840 --> 00:36:21,880
shouldn't we do something about it?

631
00:36:21,880 --> 00:36:22,920
Yes, yes, yes.

632
00:36:22,920 --> 00:36:23,920
After all that you said,

633
00:36:23,920 --> 00:36:26,320
isn't it just asking us to investigate the stolen manhole covers?

634
00:36:26,440 --> 00:36:28,000
But usually, investigating stolen manhole covers

635
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:29,719
is the job of the local police station, right?

636
00:36:30,199 --> 00:36:32,360
Yeah, just let them handle it.

637
00:36:33,880 --> 00:36:35,920
What kind of attitude is this from you three?

638
00:36:35,920 --> 00:36:37,159
What kind of attitude is that?

639
00:36:37,159 --> 00:36:38,920
I'm embarrassed for you.

640
00:36:40,320 --> 00:36:41,119
What's wrong?

641
00:36:41,280 --> 00:36:42,239
The police station and the criminal investigation team

642
00:36:42,239 --> 00:36:43,559
aren't they both part of the public security system?

643
00:36:43,559 --> 00:36:45,119
If the police station doesn't have enough people,

644
00:36:45,119 --> 00:36:46,760
should the criminal investigation team just sit by and do nothing?

645
00:36:46,760 --> 00:36:48,280
But we don't have enough people either.

646
00:36:48,280 --> 00:36:49,599
We have five cases, look.

647
00:36:49,599 --> 00:36:50,199
Just last month's cases alone...

648
00:36:50,199 --> 00:36:50,960
Are we investigating or not?

649
00:36:50,960 --> 00:36:51,639
Investigate.

650
00:36:54,760 --> 00:36:55,840
If it needs to be investigated, then investigate.

651
00:37:14,199 --> 00:37:14,920
Sir,

652
00:37:14,920 --> 00:37:17,079
May I ask how many have gone missing around here?

653
00:37:17,320 --> 00:37:18,679
Twenty-one on this road.

654
00:37:18,880 --> 00:37:19,760
Twenty-one?

655
00:37:24,400 --> 00:37:24,840
Sir,

656
00:37:24,840 --> 00:37:27,039
Why don't we try to check the nearby surveillance cameras?

657
00:37:27,360 --> 00:37:28,519
How many people in the group?

658
00:37:28,960 --> 00:37:31,679
They were pushing carts and wearing hats, couldn't see their faces.

659
00:37:32,320 --> 00:37:33,559
Sir, you saw them?

660
00:37:33,840 --> 00:37:35,360
Yes, I have "Sky Eye" (surveillance access).

661
00:37:38,719 --> 00:37:40,880
Should we stake out the intersection tonight?

662
00:37:48,639 --> 00:37:50,480
Go on, don't come back.

663
00:38:18,760 --> 00:38:20,960
Ziqing, I...

664
00:38:27,800 --> 00:38:30,039
Sir, can I make one more call?

665
00:38:30,039 --> 00:38:30,679
No problem.

666
00:38:30,679 --> 00:38:31,480
Thank you.

667
00:38:51,679 --> 00:38:52,679
Is the boss here?

668
00:38:52,960 --> 00:38:54,440
What's up? Is there something you need?

669
00:38:55,719 --> 00:38:56,679
Do you take scrap iron?

670
00:38:57,119 --> 00:38:58,440
Yes, how much do you have?

671
00:38:59,239 --> 00:39:00,239
About ten tons.

672
00:39:01,400 --> 00:39:03,199
Wait a moment, I'll make a call.

673
00:39:09,480 --> 00:39:10,599
Our boss is here.

674
00:39:11,840 --> 00:39:12,639
Hello.

675
00:39:13,119 --> 00:39:14,400
Who did you sell to before?

676
00:39:15,119 --> 00:39:16,440
Qi River Steel Market.

677
00:39:17,199 --> 00:39:18,719
Do you want manhole covers?

678
00:39:19,000 --> 00:39:20,679
Yes, but they need to be broken up.

679
00:39:21,039 --> 00:39:22,079
No need to register, right?

680
00:39:22,159 --> 00:39:23,320
Don't worry, no need.

681
00:39:23,320 --> 00:39:24,760
Just deliver them here after ten o'clock.

682
00:39:25,519 --> 00:39:26,719
Okay, I'll come find you tonight.

683
00:39:26,719 --> 00:39:27,360
Alright.

684
00:39:36,719 --> 00:39:37,519
Who is this?

685
00:39:37,880 --> 00:39:38,519
Ziming.

686
00:39:46,320 --> 00:39:47,920
I'm still in debt right now.

687
00:39:49,119 --> 00:39:51,440
So I can only find you something like this.

688
00:39:52,280 --> 00:39:54,679
Once things get a bit better for me, I'll get you a better one.

689
00:39:55,280 --> 00:39:56,519
This is pretty good.

690
00:39:56,760 --> 00:39:58,119
I'll just take a few days to rest.

691
00:39:58,440 --> 00:39:59,079
Um...

692
00:40:00,559 --> 00:40:02,760
Your sister is really nice.

693
00:40:03,559 --> 00:40:04,239
She's nice.

694
00:40:06,400 --> 00:40:08,880
I want to apologize to her in person.

695
00:40:12,280 --> 00:40:13,760
If you really care about her,

696
00:40:15,440 --> 00:40:16,679
don't contact her again.

697
00:40:18,840 --> 00:40:20,760
You just don't trust me, I...

698
00:40:22,760 --> 00:40:25,119
Yes, the things I did before,

699
00:40:25,119 --> 00:40:28,559
I really wasn't worthy of your trust.

700
00:40:29,760 --> 00:40:31,480
So what are your plans next?

701
00:40:32,719 --> 00:40:33,880
I'll just see what comes up.

702
00:40:33,880 --> 00:40:34,480
Um...

703
00:40:36,599 --> 00:40:39,320
Those old friends who do business,

704
00:40:40,440 --> 00:40:42,159
I'll see if there's anything I can do.

705
00:40:42,599 --> 00:40:44,159
A few days ago, I asked a friend.

706
00:40:45,000 --> 00:40:45,920
He opened a restaurant.

707
00:40:46,400 --> 00:40:47,960
He needs a lobby manager.

708
00:40:49,960 --> 00:40:51,639
That's not for me, I can't do that.

709
00:40:53,320 --> 00:40:55,159
Me, working as a lobby manager for someone else?

710
00:40:55,599 --> 00:40:56,559
What else can you do?

711
00:40:57,239 --> 00:41:00,360
I'm used to being the boss.

712
00:41:00,360 --> 00:41:01,920
Now you want me to work for someone else?

713
00:41:02,159 --> 00:41:04,000
I still have to start my own company.

714
00:41:04,480 --> 00:41:05,599
Do you have the capital?

715
00:41:09,920 --> 00:41:10,920
I'll raise the capital.

716
00:41:10,920 --> 00:41:12,880
I was just too conservative before.

717
00:41:16,000 --> 00:41:17,239
What are you laughing at?

718
00:41:17,960 --> 00:41:18,920
You don't believe in me.

719
00:41:24,800 --> 00:41:26,880
This is the phone Tingting used.

720
00:41:27,199 --> 00:41:28,519
I put a new SIM card in it for you.

721
00:41:29,280 --> 00:41:30,079
Charger.

722
00:41:33,400 --> 00:41:34,199
Brother-in-law.

723
00:41:35,719 --> 00:41:39,119
Don’t contact those old friends anymore.

724
00:41:39,880 --> 00:41:40,920
Don’t worry, don’t worry.

725
00:41:41,079 --> 00:41:43,280
Report to the police station on time.

726
00:41:45,039 --> 00:41:46,440
I have something to do, I’ll go first.

727
00:41:47,039 --> 00:41:48,800
I’ll treat you to a meal another day.

728
00:41:50,440 --> 00:41:51,000
Goodbye.

729
00:42:08,639 --> 00:42:09,440
Boss.

730
00:42:10,719 --> 00:42:11,480
Boss.

731
00:42:11,480 --> 00:42:12,079
Coming.

732
00:42:13,079 --> 00:42:13,880
Here I am.

733
00:42:13,880 --> 00:42:14,679
Where’s the goods?

734
00:42:15,519 --> 00:42:16,960
They’re in the back, the truck will be here soon.

735
00:42:17,400 --> 00:42:18,920
Where are you unloading this time?

736
00:42:19,360 --> 00:42:20,079
Right here.

737
00:42:20,079 --> 00:42:21,000
How is that possible?

738
00:42:21,400 --> 00:42:22,559
Where are you putting it? You have to tell me.

739
00:42:22,559 --> 00:42:23,960
See if the vehicle can get in.

740
00:42:23,960 --> 00:42:24,760
Don’t worry.

741
00:42:27,679 --> 00:42:28,320
Here.

742
00:42:28,519 --> 00:42:29,920
Even a tricycle can get in here.

743
00:42:32,119 --> 00:42:33,679
We’ll put it here in a bit.

744
00:42:34,079 --> 00:42:35,400
They’re all smashed up, right?

745
00:42:38,800 --> 00:42:39,840
Did you smash them all?

746
00:42:40,920 --> 00:42:41,760
Yes, all smashed.

747
00:42:41,760 --> 00:42:42,559
As long as they’re smashed, that’s fine.

748
00:42:44,320 --> 00:42:45,480
There are also cables.

749
00:42:46,880 --> 00:42:48,159
Where did all this come from?

750
00:42:48,800 --> 00:42:50,199
Our industry rules—

751
00:42:50,320 --> 00:42:52,800
We only ask about the price of what we buy,

752
00:42:52,800 --> 00:42:53,760
not where it came from.

753
00:42:54,079 --> 00:42:54,880
Understood.

754
00:42:55,639 --> 00:42:57,280
Hey, hurry up and call to check on it.

755
00:42:57,280 --> 00:42:58,239
I still have things to do.

756
00:42:58,239 --> 00:42:59,480
Alright, got it.
